title: For Sale:  Heckler & Koch VP-70
postcontent:
I have an H&K VP70 Z if you are not familiar with what this pistol is then he is a short history lesson.
It was the first polymer-framed pistol, 12 years before the Glock 17. The VP70 uses a spring-loaded striker like a Glock, instead of a conventional firing pin. It is double action only so the trigger pull is relatively heavy. In lieu of a blade front sight, the VP70 uses a polished ramp with a central notch in the middle to provide the illusion of a dark front post. The VP70 does have a manual safety. It is the circular button located immediately behind the trigger and is a common cross-block safety. The "Z" designates the civilian variant is a semiautomatic only version. The VP70 was produced from 1970 until 1989.
This pistol is chambered in 9x19mm Para. For the pistol it comes with two original magazines. I believe all are 21 round magazines. The HK VP-70 Z in 9x19mm comes in a 1970’s pristine box that is still dark grey, magazine loader tool, has the original target from the factory in a wax package and the original operation manual.

title: For Sale:  Heckler & Koch VP-70 Z
postcontent:
I have an H&K VP70 Z if you are not familiar with what this pistol is then he is a short history lesson.
It was the first polymer-framed pistol, 12 years before the Glock 17. The VP70 uses a spring-loaded striker like a Glock, instead of a conventional firing pin. It is double action only so the trigger pull is relatively heavy. In lieu of a blade front sight, the VP70 uses a polished ramp with a central notch in the middle to provide the illusion of a dark front post. The VP70 does have a manual safety. It is the circular button located immediately behind the trigger and is a common cross-block safety. The "Z" designates the civilian variant is a semiautomatic only version. The VP70 was produced from 1970 until 1989. Four hundred VP-70 Z pistols were made chambered in 9×21mm IMI; these samples were made primarily for the civilian market of Italy, where the use of the 9×19mm Para is a sole privilege of military and law enforcement agencies.
This pistol is chambered 9x21mm. For this HK VP-70 Z pistol comes with three magazines. I believe all are 21 round magazines. The 9x21mm comes in lighter grey more warn box that is still strong just lighter than the other pistol I have listed. Included with this is 500 rounds of 9x21mm ammunition.
Thank you for looking and please let me know if you have any questions.
Sorry not interested in trades at this time.
If this is to be transferred inside of Iowa it has to be with another CCW holder, if you currently do not have your CCW then we will have to use a local FFL for the paperwork. If this is going from one state to another then it will absolutely have to be from one FFL to another FFL. No exceptions.

title: For Sale:  Mossberg Chainsaw 500
postcontent: New in box, never fired.Certainly one of the most unusual-looking guns to come out is the Mossberg 500 Chainsaw. Built in the iconic Mossberg 500 action, the Chainsaw is a pistol-grip pump-action shotgun with no stock. While guns like this are desirable for home defense, they're notoriously hard to control while firing, a problem that Mossberg has solved by attaching a wrap-around chainsaw-style hand grip to the pump. Intended to be fired from the hip, this top handle allows the user to cycle the action while simultaneously maintaining leverage above the gun to help tame muzzle flip. In addition to the chainsaw-style grip, the 500 Chainsaw has a stand-off barrel that can be used to breech doors and three rails that can mount accessories.
